(The) Four Tops are an American vocal quartet, whose 
repertoire has included doo-wop, jazz, soul music, R&B, disco, 
adult contemporary, and showtunes. Founded in Detroit, Michigan 
as The Four Aims, lead singer Levi Stubbs [born Levi Stubbles, 
a cousin of Jackie Wilson and brother of The Falcons' Joe Stubbs]
and groupmates Abdul "Duke" Fakir, Renaldo "Obie" Benson and 
Lawrence Payton remained together for over four decades, having 
gone from 1953 until 1997 without a single change in personnel.
